message:
type: SPEC
files: src/click/core.py
spec: Add batch_size support to Option (multiple=True chunked processing).

1) Option.__init__ signature: add new kwarg 'batch_size: int | None = None' (place it near 'count: bool = False' / 'multiple: bool = False' params). Store 'self.batch_size = batch_size' after the super().__init__(...) call.

2) Validation, inside the existing 'if __debug__:' block in Option.__init__ (same block that validates self.count/self.multiple etc.), add:
    if self.batch_size is not None:
        if not self.multiple:
            raise TypeError("'batch_size' is only valid with 'multiple'.")
        if self.batch_size < 0:
            raise ValueError("'batch_size' must be a positive integer.")

3) Option.to_info_dict: add 'batch_size=self.batch_size' to the info_dict.update(...) call, unconditionally (so the key is always present in the dict, including when batch_size is None/unset).

4) Parameter.type_cast_value (base Parameter class, ~line 2334, the 'if self.multiple:' branch that currently does 'return tuple(convert(x) for x in check_iter(value))'): change so that when a batch_size is configured (use getattr(self, 'batch_size', None) since only Option has this attr, Argument does not), it chunks the converted tuple into sub-tuples of up to batch_size items, e.g.:

    if self.multiple:
        converted = tuple(convert(x) for x in check_iter(value))
        batch_size = getattr(self, 'batch_size', None)
        if batch_size:
            return tuple(
                converted[i : i + batch_size]
                for i in range(0, len(converted), batch_size)
            )
        return converted

No other files needed for this feature on my end (I do not need types.py). Please ACK with a CLAIM echoing this so I know you'll implement it; I will not touch core.py.
